response.original_title: Róisín and Chiara: Back to Back
response.overview: Róisín and Chiara describe themselves as a ‘slightly twisted blend of The Mighty Boosh, House of Pain and James Joyce’.  This implies a low-impact, high-brow experience when in reality any pretensions are best left as you enter the Botego, the subterranean venue that provides a dungeon-like background to their comic odyssey.  Indeed, the faint hearted may indeed wish to escape.
